      "description": "Available is an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, maintained to museum standards. This example features the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, delivering linear power through a crisp 5-speed manual gearbox. The chassis remains structurally flawless, retaining its original double-wishbone aluminum suspension and a perfectly balanced 50/50 weight distribution. Mechanically pristine, the Torsen limited-slip differential and cooling system are strictly factory-spec, ensuring peak thermal efficiency and cornering precision. With zero aftermarket modifications and a documented service history confirming optimal compression across all rotor faces, this FD represents the pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering in its purest form.",
